Adjust rack to middle position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry all
produce. In a #small bowl{}, combine @Hoisin Sauce{2%tablespoon}, @Ketchup{2%tablespoon},
half the @Brown Sugar{1%tablespoon}, and 1 tsp @White Wine Vinegar{5%teaspoon}
(2 tsp for 4 servings). Pat @Pork Tenderloin{12%ounce} dry with paper towels
and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Place on a lightly oiled #baking sheet{}.
Roast until almost cooked through, ~{18-20%minutes}.

Meanwhile, peel and mince or grate @Ginger{1%thumb}. Melt @Butter{1%tablespoon}
in a #small pot{} over medium-high heat. Add half the ginger; cook until fragrant,
~{20-30%seconds}. Add @Jasmine Rice{1/2%cup}, 3/4 cup water (1 1/2 cups for 4
servings), and a pinch of salt. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low
simmer. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}. Keep covered off heat until
ready to serve.

Core, deseed, and thinly slice @Bell Pepper{1}(core deseeded and sliced). Trim
@Green Beans{6%ounce}(trimmed). Mince @Garlic{2%clove}(minced). Place
@Persian Cucumber{2}(whole) under a #plate{}; press down until cucumbers break
open. Chop into 1-inch pieces. In a #medium bowl{}, combine @Sesame Oil{1%tablespoon},
1/2 tsp garlic (1 tsp for 4), remaining vinegar and brown sugar, and half the
@Soy Sauce{4%tablespoon}. Add cucumbers; toss to coat. Season with salt, pepper,
and @?Korean Chili Flakes{1%teaspoon} to taste.

Once pork is almost cooked through, remove baking sheet from oven. Heat broiler
to high or oven to 500 degrees. Brush pork with a layer of hoisin glaze (save the
rest for serving). Broil or roast until pork is cooked through and glaze is tacky
and lightly charred, ~{2-3%minutes} more. Set aside on a #cutting board{} to rest.

In a second small bowl, stir together @Cornstarch{1%teaspoon}, remaining soy
sauce, and 2 TBSP warm water (¼ cup for 4); add remaining garlic and ginger.
Heat a large drizzle of @Vegetable Oil{1%tablespoon} in a #large pan{} over
medium-high heat. Add bell pepper and green beans; cook until browned and
tender, ~{7-9%minutes}. Add soy sauce mixture; cook until veggies are glazed,
~{1-2%minutes}. Stir in @Cashews{1%ounce}. Season with salt and pepper.

> If sauce is too thick, stir in water 1 TBSP at a time until stir-fry is fully coated.

Fluff rice with a #fork{}; season with salt and pepper. Thinly slice pork crosswise.
Divide rice, pork, and veggies between plates. Drizzle pork with reserved hoisin
glaze. Garnish with @Sesame Seeds{1%tablespoon} as you like. Serve cucumber salad
on the side.